A "particle" is that thingy that moves around in the billiard. It always moves with velocity of measure 1, by convention.  Currently there are two types of particles:   Particle , which propagates as a straight line.  MagneticParticle , which propagates as a circle instead of a line (similar to electrons in a perpendicular magnetic field).   There are two ways to create a particle. The first one is to provide the constructor with some initial conditions:  x0   =   rand ();   y0   =   rand ();  φ0   =   2 π * rand ()  p   =   Particle ( x0 ,   y0 ,   φ0 )   Particle{Float64}
